<br>
If you're looking for pure sustainable solo power, root/rot or quadding, spend your first 12 arch points on MC1, SCM1, MC2, and SCM2.  After those skills, if you are still looking for more benefit to solo quadding, do SCM3, and then the 3 SCF skills. (MC3 is simply too many AA skill points for just one more mana/tick, and can be finished up later, if at all).<br>
<br>
Tat <p>Tatanka WolfDancer, 58th Druid<BR>
